==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Way-going
<hw>Way"-go`ing</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Going away;
departing; of or pertaining to one who goes away.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Way-going crop</b></col> <fld>(Law of Leases)</fld>,
<cd>a crop of grain to which tenants for years are sometimes entitled by
custom; grain sown in the fall to be reaped at the next harvest; a crop
which will not ripen until after the termination of the lease.</cd>
<au>Burrill.</au></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Way-goose</ent>⟦br⟧
